cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning-based AutoML framework for network quantization and binarization, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed framework is evaluated on various CNN models, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI-based approach for automating the design space exploration of network quantization and binarization. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The proposed framework is aimed at achieving hardware-friendly deep learning on mobile devices, which involves optimizing the hardware architecture for efficient inference. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves optimizing the system (i.e., the network architecture and hardware) for efficient inference on mobile devices.
